24/Dec/24 3:22 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;Hi,

Â 

we have discussed this defect together with Gaurab from Amdocs in one of the sessions, last week, in which we analysed E2E the expected behaviour and discussed some defects.

Also Waldemar and Michael Heller were involved.

Â 

1. What I miss in this error description is the EXACT activities, that the agent/tester has done.

my assumption is:Â  the agent has selected the unsharp sim swap (which is a possibility in Retail, that will disappear with the esim Push Epic, but is still available if the permission for insert sim_serial_number is set (I think)

so..Â  question:Â  did indeed the tester select the UNSHARP SIMSWAP?

Â 

Because:

IF Agent selects UNSHARP SIMSWAP,Â 

THEN SubmitOrder.SIMCARD = E (as it always was)

and... OGW is triggered to send the emails when SIMCARD =E

(so.. this is not correct)

Â 

AS AGREED WITH GAURAB :

Amdocs will change/improve the software:

OGW will not only check for SIMCARD = E,Â  but will also check whether the NEW_SIM_SERIAL_NUMBER is not populated.

only then the emails will be sent;;;

column791:
13/Jan/25 8:46 PM;robert.goebbels@vodafone.com;So final outcomeÂ  (my understanding)

Summary:Â 
 * works as (wrongly) designed
 * Amdocs will fix this without the need of a Change Request
 ** OGW will not only check:Â  is SIMTYPE E, in order to trigger the emails, BUT also check if the SIMNumber is empty

Â 

Details:

RETAIL channel; blocking permissions set:
 * agent must therefore insert SIM number (instead of SIMTYPE) AND
 * agent has possiblity to select Sharp vs unsharp simswapÂ 

Omnius sends in submit Order
 * SIMYPE E, because agent has selected unsharp SIMSWAP (not clear to me, but it looks like Omnius also sends SIMTYPE E, if the agent selected sharp SIMSWAP, if I understand the comments right).Â 
 * SIMSERIAL number (because Agent has inserted a (physical) SIMnumberÂ 

OGW triggers 5910 and/or 5930 email although the agent has inserted a (physical)Â  sim number

Â 

Solution: Even if Omnius sends SIMTYPE E,Â  OGW must also check, if a SIMNumber is providedÂ  in submitOrder.Â  if the simnumber is empty, only then trigger the emailsÂ 

-->Â  as aligned with Gaurab some weeks ago

Â 

Â ;;;

column775:
14/Aug/24 1:47 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;As Discussed, post the OGW changes related to FastSearch flow-- we have the below current valid behavior:
Below Flow flow will be always triggered until OGW keeps receiving Intermediate status as "Customer created" from DSL backend
DSL--> OGW will call In progress (Customer created) status
OGW-->OneDMS Will call: In Progress Doc-Archiving(internally it will call FastSearch/Save Document
As per the BAU flow from DSL backend systems-- they will be sending the above intermediate status of customer created--multiple times to keep updating OGW about customer creation until they complete the order and send ORDER_COMPLETED status to OGW.
OGW will stop calling InProgress Doc Archiving status as soon as it receives the updated status as "ORDER_COMPLETED"
Bottomline: Multiple In Progress Doc Archiving status call are expected from OGW -->OneDMS --as DSL backend will be sending this intermediate status to OGW until the Order is getting completed at backend.;;;

 * plan how to execute and run pipeline to remove and setup new xmlstarlet software is missing
 * is it required for full flow setup to build the application again on sandbox server (i.e php,nginx,ose and solstice deployment again)Â

column771:
28/Aug/24 4:13 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Feedback from Pritam



Reason for PCAT issue is:Â 
 # On RHEL 8 the xml2 entity is not compatible. (xml2 is the utility which helps to parse the XML file on unix/Linux system)
 # So, the compatible utility for RHEL 8 is XML STARLET
 # We have installed it on the server.
 # However, in the application where we use the pcat_import.sh script to import the PCAT, xml2 utility was used to parse the xml files which is compatible with RHEL8.
 # Now the issue is, on ACC3 SB we have RHEL 8 (we need XML STARLET here) and on rest of all environments including prod we have RHEL7 (we have xml2 working)
 # So, to use this XML STARLET only in ACC3 SB there must be change in code, but this will break the other running environment including PROD.
 # To avoid this, we have received an additional file/script from tech m, only for ACC3 SB,Â  to be copied after deployment so it will use the mistarget utility to parse the file (loca.xml,sandbox.xml etc.)

So, in conclusion we have received the solution but is not rolled out or included in the standard s/w delivery. In my view this will be added once we upgrade all our environments to RHEL8.

Additional info from Pramod:Â we need to replace the import_full.sh file after every full deployment which was provided by Deepika to which support xmlstarlet to import the pcat files and publish it in ACC3 env. This new import_full.sh are not included in their code due to platform difference between SIT , ACC and Prod;;;

column764:
09/Jul/24 5:15 PM;natasa.dimovic1@vodafone.com;Analysis on PCAT side was done by [~tobias.pohlmann@vodafone.com] :

Hi, Ariadne,

{*}{color:#de350b}yes, I can confirm that in any case where we book KIP + TV (no matter if Broadvision or not, no matter which order we book it in), no technician section should be shown{color}{*}.Â 

The reason why this fails is as I tried to point out in my comment below. It really is pretty confusing, I apologize for that. I had a call with Natasa where I explained the problem, because it really is a bit hard to grasp.

So again in case of Broadvision what happens is:
 - [In the KIP package]Â KIP is booked, TV Connect is added because of Broadvision ---> OSF understands that no section for KIP should be shown because KIP + TV is booked and remembers that

 - [In the TV package]Â TV Digital is booked ---> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked

==> no KIP or TV technician section is shown

In case of Not-Broadvision:
 - [In the KIP package]Â Only KIP is booked, but not TV yet ----> OSF supposes that a technician section should be shown for KIP (because only KIP is booked) and remembers that
 - [In the TV package]Â TV Digital + TV Connect is booked ----> OSF understands that no section for TV should be shown because KIP+TV is booked, but doesn't update the reasoning for KIP

==> technician section is shown for KIP, but not for TV;;;

However, for these Fusion C switches we had topics in scope for different releases, so the functionality itself is live since a long time but with a technical go live.

1)[OS-8975] SOL0 - Search & display customer with product(s) mastered in solstice - Vodafone Global Jira -> implemented with Wave 7.0, tested with Wave 7.1 Â 

2) [OS-11283] SOL1SE32 - Extending the OSF Search for Solstice Customers - Vodafone Global Jira -> initially implemented with Wave 7.2, because of needed enhancement tested again with Wave 9.0Â 

We are not having any new functionality, the switches are there since years.Â 
To retest your TechM fix for OS-56961 of course all switches had to be YES and in release Wave 9.0 they have been on YES in general most of the time, as OS-11283 was part of Wave 9.0 and tested by Fusion C team.

As ACC1 was used for Wave 8.2 of course ACC1 was different, as there only OS-8975 was live already (therefore only one switch was enabled)Â 

And as its technically live, Fusion C team can decide at any time to switch it ON in production. Its like any other technical go live, where functionaly is enabled in ACC but not yet in production.;;;

column1: NEW CR OSF | ACC1 | Wave 8.2 | sliding prices are not interpreted as expected
column41:
{color:#ff0000}The priority is set to "Blocker" as the issue is a show stopper for the Go Live of : [https://de.jira.agile.vodafone.com/browse/PORPDT-79] 
Without a fix the feature can not be deployed into production.{color}

Â 

Test data:

Browser: Chrome
Environment: ACC1 
Channel: Telesales + Retail

Steps to reproduce the issue:
 - Enter address: Goethestr. 27 26409 Wittmund Wittmund
 - Select package: "Kabel Internet & Phone"
 - Select tariff: "[3BV:B09] GigaZuhause 250 Kabel, 1.-9. Monat 19,99 â‚¬"
 - Select goody on "Gutschriften und Aktionen" section: "[JL5] Gutschrift GigaZuhause Young: 1.-9. Monat: 0 â‚¬, 10.-24. Monat: -5 â‚¬, danach 0 â‚¬"
 - open basket

The prices are not calculated as expected.
As a consequence of the wrong basket also the contract summary is incorrect.

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=856,height=463! Â 

+Pre-Analyses of product configuration team:+
OSF uses the 'Price sliding' field from the Product Catalog to configure the way the price periods are shown in the frontend:

!screenshot-1.png|width=338,height=226!

The numbers in this field are however interpreted as absolute points in time. They should however be interpreted as relative time intervals.

+Concretely this means:+

Price sliding '9:6:' should be interpreted as 0.-9. month, 10.-15. month, 16. month onward.
Currently it is interpreted as 0.-9. month, 0.-6. month, whatever comes afterward.
This obviously does not make any sense, since the second period ends before the first one, so the consequence in the frontend is, that the second period is ignored.

+The obvious fix therefore is:+
The numbers in the "Price sliding" field should always be interpreted as *relative time* intervalls.

Â 

+Additional proof:+
When checking in the OSF Backoffice for the product properties, the price_sliding of JL5 looks like this:

!image-2024-04-09-15-34-39-869.png!

Looking at this in overview in the frontend, the second time intervall seems to be ignored:

!image-2024-04-10-18-00-56-136.png|width=423,height=229!

Manually changing it to 15 then leads to the following view in OSF:

!image-2024-04-09-15-42-29-039.png|width=737,height=206!

This is, however, still wrong. OSF seems to tread the numbers in the PCAT import as absolute times instead of relative intervals

=> Three sliding prices are in principle possible to show, but the configuration in the product setup is imported and interpreted wrongly
